<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2018-11-29</DATELINE><TITLE>Infection in Renal Transplant Recipients</TITLE><BODY>Infections are a major cause of morbidity and mortality in renal transplant recipients. This chapter reviews major risk factors for infection as well as important preventive measures. More common infections, including cytomegalovirus and urinary tract infection, are reviewed in detail.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>